# Automated PR Review Gate (Pre-Merge)

Before merging any PR to `main`, **trigger and fully resolve all automated review feedback** on that PR.

## Bots / sources in scope

Address findings from **all** of these when present:

- **CodeRabbit** (`coderabbitai`)
- **CodeAntai** / Code Antai (and similarly named AI reviewers)
- Other automated PR reviewers that post inline or summary comments (e.g. Socket Security actionable items when they block merge, Cursor Bugbot when requested)

Human review comments that request concrete fixes are also in scope when they are open on the PR.

## Scope (mandatory)

Address **every** item, including:

- Critical / high / medium findings
- **Nitpicks**
- **Outside-of-diff-range** comments
- Suggestions, refactors, and doc notes from the reviewer

## Workflow (loop until clear)

1. After pushing PR updates, wait for / re-request review when available (`@coderabbitai review`, etc.).
2. Collect **all** review threads (inline + summary + out-of-range) from every in-scope bot.
3. For each item: fix in code/docs, or reply with a clear English rationale if intentionally deferred (rare — prefer fixing).
4. Push follow-up commits; re-request review; **repeat until no new actionable comments remain**.
5. Do **not** merge while unresolved automated review comments remain.

## Exceptions

- Duplicate comments already fixed in a later commit: mark resolved and cite the commit.
- False positives: short English reply explaining why + resolve thread after confirmation.

See also English content policy `@.cursor/rules/010-english-content.mdc`.
